Visualization Problem Statement 1
PROBLEM STATEMENT:

In the United States, the use of deadly force by police has been a high-profile and contentious issue. Police killings are one of the leading causes of death in the US. The purpose of this report is to analyze the trend of fatal police shootings of fleers in the US between 2015 -2020. Studies have shown that Black, Hispanic, and Native American individuals are disproportionately stopped by police and killed in encounters. 
               At least 416 people were killed in police chases in 2017, according to an analysis of federal records by FairWarning. That’s the fourth consecutive year in which the number of people killed during police pursuits increased – and a 22% spike over 2013, when 341 people were killed, FairWarning found by analyzing National Highway Traffic Safety Administration crash records.
